section.section:
"State share of special education funding" means:
0.29 in fiscal year 2004;
0.37 in fiscal year 2005;
0.41 in fiscal year 2006;
0.46 in fiscal year 2007; and
0.50 in fiscal year 2008 and each fiscal year thereafter.

For purposes of paragraph (1) of this subsection, the minimum Tier II special education grant amount for each county is the result obtained by multiplying the Tier II special education per pupil amount by the county's special education enrollment count, and multiplying this product by:
0.50 for fiscal year 2004;
0.66 for fiscal year 2005;
0.70 for fiscal year 2006;
0.76 for fiscal year 2007; and
0.80 for fiscal year 2008 and each fiscal year thereafter.
